news.title: Registration of construction workers may see alterations in Maharashtra
news.para: The Building and Other Construction Workers' (Regulation of Employment and Conditions of Service) Act, 1996, clearly mentions the 90-day work period as a criterion.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body's budget of Rs 6,224 crore for FY24 passed without discussion
news.para: In the 2023-24 budget, the civic body has allocated 25% of its expenditure i.e., 1,530 crore for new roads, flyovers, bridges, road under bridges (RuBs), road under bridges (RoBs) and traffic signals.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body recovers Rs 101 crore property tax in FY23
news.para: Officials claimed that Rs 60 crore was still pending towards defaulters of previous years and a sealing drive would be launched to recover this amount.

news.title: ASK Property Fund exits Eldeco's project in South Delhi
news.para: The fund that had invested Rs 120 crore and has achieved an internal rate of return of 21%. The project is a commercial development comprising of retail and office spaces in South Delhi.

news.title: Architect at fault if building against approved map in Lucknow
news.para: ​During a meeting with architects’ association, LDA VC Indramani Tripathi discussed the number of pending cases of structural map approval due to incorrect filing of maps by architects, contrary to the land use.

news.title: New home sales in U.S. increase again in November 2022
news.para: New home sales increased 5.8% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 640,000 units last month, the Commerce Department said on Friday. October's sales pace was revised lower to 605,000 units from the previously reported 632,000.

news.title: Kerala government issues guidelines to update details about properties
news.para: The circular also specifically said that all types of constructions irrespective of whether they are legal or illegal should be updated.

news.title: Mangaluru police issue guidelines for hostels and PGs
news.para: ​The owners should furnish their details, address, phone number, identity card and register books every year, with the office of the city police commissioner, as well as at the jurisdictional police station.

news.title: CAG flags various issues in Nagpur metro project, says MMRCL could not monetize land parcels
news.para: In the report, the CAG observed, as per the detailed project report, the commercial operation of phase 1 was to be achieved by April 2018 but only two out of four Reaches have begun commercial operation.

news.title: Hefty fees keep property owners away from Gunthewari scheme in Pune
news.para: According to the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC)'s data, residents seeking regularisation of unauthorised properties would have to pay three times the ready reckoner rates for getting the proposal approved.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation asks residents to link ration card details with property tax number
news.para: Commercial building owners have been asked to link their PAN card details or GST number with the property tax number.

news.title: Real estate sector grows apace in current financial year in Jaipur
news.para: Sharad Mehra, inspector general, registration & stamps, said, “The real estate sector has witnessed strong growth, reflecting the increase in revenue collections. If the trend continues, which is likely, the department will reach near the target set for the current financial year.”

news.title: Home registration in Kolkata up 167% year-on-year in November 2022
news.para: Since the initial stamp duty cut announcement in July 2021, a whopping 72,790 residential properties have been registered in the city in these 17 months. The preceding 17 months prior to the introduction of rebate saw registration of only 44,736 units.

news.title: Adani Group offers to relocate employees after cement plants' closure
news.para: The statement stated that 85 employees of Darlaghat plant in Solan and 58 from Barmana plant in Bilaspur would be relocated to nearby sister plants of Adani group.

news.title: Kochi: Assets of Holy Faith H2O builders to be auctioned
news.para: Holy faith H20 was the first building razed on January 11, 2020. The auction will be held on January 20 next year to realize Rs 42 crore.
